<div style="max-width: 600px; margin: 0 auto; font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, sans-serif; color: #1f2937;">
  <div style="padding: 32px 24px;">
    <h1 style="font-size: 22px; font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: 16px; color: #b91c1c;">
      Seat sync failed (revenue-leak alert)
    </h1>

    <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.6; color: #4b5563; margin-bottom: 16px;">
      Stripe rejected a seat-count update for <strong><%= @org.name %></strong>
      (id <code><%= @org.id %></code>). The org's local seat count was applied but
      the Stripe subscription was NOT updated, so they may be under-charged this period.
    </p>

    <p style="font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.6; color: #4b5563; margin-bottom: 24px;">
      <strong>Stripe error:</strong><br>
      <code style="display: block; background: #f3f4f6; padding: 12px; border-radius: 6px; word-break: break-all;"><%= @error_message %></code>
    </p>

    <p style="font-size: 14px; color: #6b7280; line-height: 1.5;">
      Resolve by reconciling the seat count manually in the Stripe dashboard, then
      re-running <code>Stripe::SeatSyncService.call(Organization.find(<%= @org.id %>))</code>.
    </p>
  </div>
</div>
